programme.title: Coast vs Country
programme.desc: Kerr Drummond and Sara Damergi help retired Swanscombe couple Roger and Anne move somewhere more peaceful after living in the same house for the last 42 years.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Sara Damergi helps find a suitable property for Mark and Wendy Lang, a couple from Liverpool with a £90,000 budget who want to start a new life on Spain's Costa Almeria.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away
programme.desc: A couple want a rural holiday home, but are divided as to where. John McMahon wants to buy a place in the Llyn Peninsula in north Wales, where his rowing club is based, while his wife Elaine would prefer the warm climate and cultured atmosphere of France's Cote d'Azur. Laura Hamilton and Adrian Simpson help them to resolve the dilemma.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four hosts - Michelle Pannell, Tony Brooks, Gary Clark and Ami Mehta - compete to host the best dinner party in Chelmsford and Brentwood, Essex. One serves kebabs, while another has a staff of seven on hand at her wealthy home. Goat soup and a 1980s-inspired menu are also in store for the diners.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Entrepreneur Rob Earnshaw, competitive foodie Nigel Thompson, `posh Geordie' Becky Mortimer and down-to-earth Sunderland lass Karina Armstrong compete for the prize in Tyne and Wear. Featuring a globe-trotting menu, some peculiar culinary mash-ups, a fiery starter and an emotional finale.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp and Phil Spencer head to Devon, where they help local newlyweds Sam and Jamie, who are looking to start afresh in a new home and put a difficult two years behind them. Plus, Sharon wants to move to Torquay with husband Geoff, as well as her children and mother, but the couple have never viewed a house together and it soon becomes apparent the property experts will have a tough time persuading them to agree on a new home.(n)

programme.title: Kirstie's Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp devises presents for her friends and family, focusing on alternatives to high-street shopping. She visits a woman in Devon and picks up the ingredients to create her own soap. Later she prepares chutney, and learns the art of teddy bear-making and how to stitch a stocking to hang above the fireplace.(n)

programme.title: Jamie's Christmas with Bells On
programme.desc: Part two of two. Having taken care of the preparation in the first show, Jamie Oliver now brings everything together for the perfect Christmas Day feast, putting a new twist on Brussels sprouts, making tacos and other snacks, and even spicing up the wine. Finally, he demonstrates how to make the best of leftovers with his Boxing Day turkey chowder.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Jonnie Irwin helps Steven Weald and Sue Upson search for a winter home north of Naples on Florida's Gulf Coast, and shows the active couple five properties that are within their £150,000 budget.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Entrepreneur and sports fishing enthusiast Ian Walls from Edinburgh has decided to expand his property portfolio by purchasing a place on Grand Bahama where he can spend a couple of months every winter. With his US-based girlfriend Lisa on hand to offer a second opinion, Sara Damergi shows them a selection of homes for sale around his £111,000 budget.(n)

programme.title: Jamie's Ultimate Christmas
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver has been cooking and experimenting with classic Christmas food for over two decades and this programme pulls together his knowledge and experience to bring the very best of the season. He begins with what he calls the three foundations of Christmas, with guests will forgiving any mistakes as long as the turkey is succulent, the gravy is tasty, and the roast potatoes are perfect, and serves the main course with Brussels sprouts done with chorizo and chestnuts, and glazed carrots. Jamie also shares some other dishes, including gravadlax steeped in a beetroot, horseradish and vodka marinade, as well as gooey chocolate pots, turkey risotto, cocktails, and a classic beef Wellington.(n)

programme.title: Kirstie's Handmade Christmas
programme.desc: Kirstie heads to the Waddesdon Manor Christmas Fair in Buckinghamshire, visiting countless Christmas stalls with thousands of homemade culinary delights and handcrafted seasonal gifts. Later, Kirstie tries her hand at some Christmas crafts, creating handmade decorations and presents, along with an array of festive food.(n)

programme.title: It Was Alright In
programme.desc: Matt Lucas narrates this look at the programmes that flirted with danger during the decade, including Blue Peter, which carried on filming as a fire broke out live on air, while The Fun of the Fair showed teenage girls riding motorcycles through burning hoops. At the same time government-produced public information films petrified viewers with scary scenarios of possible accidents in the home. Contributors include Robin Askwith, Liza Goddard, Oona King, Clive Anderson, Philippa Perry, Samira Ahmed, Ellie Taylor and Angela Barnes.(n)

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: A 61-year-old woman is airlifted to hospital after a car mounted the pavement and ran her over and doctors quickly get her into the CT scanner to ascertain the full extent of her injuries. Elsewhere, 91-year-old Sam arrives after suffering a suspected stroke, and four-month-old boy Teddy is rushed in after falling face first out of his car seat, hitting the pavement.(n)

programme.title: Derren Brown: Miracle
programme.desc: The award-winning hypnotist, mindreader and master of psychological illusion returns to the stage with a show that explores the world of evangelical faith healing, with Derren selecting people from the audience with a variety of ailments and attempting to rectify their problems using only the power of faith and the laying on of hands. The spectacle was created by Derren and his long-time collaborators Andy Nyman and Andrew O'Connor and was filmed over two nights at the Palace Theatre in London's West End.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Wildest Weather
programme.desc: Footage of unusual weather conditions recorded in Britain during 2016, and exploring the factors that led to these incidents. The programme features footage recorded by people caught in the middle of floods, super-storms, tornadoes and lightning strikes, as well as a look at how a record level El Nino effect altered Britain's weather.(n)

programme.title: Alan Carr's 12 Stars of Christmas
programme.desc: Alan turns festive elf as he hosts a star-studded quiz show in which three famous faces compete to win hundreds of presents for the studio audience, each taking it in turns to choose doors from a giant advent calendar, behind which are more celebrities armed with questions about the highlights of the past 12 months. Alesha Dixon, Rob Beckett and Alexander Armstrong take part in the first edition, with guests Miranda Hart, will.i.am, Matt Lucas, Jessica Ennis-Hill, Roger Moore, Little Mix, Bear Grylls and William Shatner asking the questions and setting the challenges.(n)

programme.title: Coast vs Country
programme.desc: Sara Damergi and Kerr Drummond help a couple who want to move to Dorset after 25 years in the same Cheltenham home.(n)

programme.title: Coast vs Country
programme.desc: Kerr Drummond and Sara Damergi help a couple search for their dream home in Dorset on a budget of £90,000, with six properties to view both on the coast and in the open countryside.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Sara Damergi helps Irene Evans search for a home in western Andalusia, Spain, within commuting distance of Gibraltar, where she hopes to find work as a paralegal. She has decided to leave the UK after a tumultuous few years and has a budget of £90,000.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Adrian Simpson meets London couple Bob and Annette Roberts, who want a retirement holiday home in Grenada, so he searches the Caribbean island for properties on a budget of £225,000.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Contestants from south-east Essex compete for the £1,000 prize, beginning with overly confident foodie James Manders who tries to emulate the fine dining of Michelin-starred restaurants. As the evenings go on, Amanda Gregory is confronted over her argumentative behaviour during Julie Tworogal's meal and Ken Greenway reveals his secret love of bats.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four contestants compete to host the best dinner party in Newcastle and Northumberland, including Bosnian-born Irena who hopes to impress with a Balkan banquet. Next to host is vintage-loving Rachel, whose twist on classic food goes down well, especially with curtain salesman John who holds his dinner party on the third night. The final meal is cooked by recruitment agency owner Michael, who decides to serve veal, venison and truffle to his guests.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp and Phil Spencer go hunting for two family homes in the north-east of England. New parents Karen and Chris are keen to return to their roots in the villages around Darlington, Co Durham, with baby Amelia. Kris and Heather have put wedding and holiday plans on hold until they find a house, but they are having trouble deciding between the city, the country or the coast.(n)

programme.title: Kirstie's Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: As Kirstie Allsopp gets ready for a Christmas party at her Devonshire cottage she panics about the food, and calls on cookery writer Amy Willcock to help prepare the turkey, while chocolatier Marc Demarquette teaches her how to create the finest chocolate truffles to satisfy her sweet-toothed guests. Candle-maker Nigel Parker demonstrates the art of creating intricate yuletide candles using moulds from old wallpaper rollers, and cracker-maker Clare Hutcheson reveals the true potential of toilet rolls. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Jamie's Festive Feast
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver prepares a variety of dishes that are ideal for lazy winter days, from simple one-pot wonders like Bloody Mary beef to winter warmers such as oozy cheesy pasta. Also on the menu are breakfast waffles with hot chocolate and fiesta tacos. Plus, ideas for party meals, from posh pork kebabs to Keralan fish curry.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Sara Damergi helps George and Gillian Pook search for a holiday home and a property they can eventually retire to on Costa Rica's Caribbean coast, and shows them places she hopes will be suitable within their £100,000 budget.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Having both retired from the Army, Rachel and Steven Grey are hoping to find the perfect property on Costa Rica's Pacific Costa Ballena where they can run a small B&B. Sara Damergi shows them a variety of possible options for their £250,000 budget.(n)

programme.title: Grand Designs: House of the Year
programme.desc: Kevin McCloud visits four more properties competing for a place on the finalist shortlist, including an open-plan family home built in a former allotment, a house made from a group of red tin pods on a piece of urban wasteland. The others are a house stitched into a wall that sits between a Zen courtyard and an English walled garden, and a large, glamorous home that creatively pulls northern light through the house. At the end of the show he announces the overall winner of the Royal Institute of British Architects House of the Year 2016. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: Festive edition of the documentary following the work of Professor Noel Fitzpatrick and his team. Charity worker Kerry brings in Maxi, a three-year old rescue greyhound with severely damaged front legs. Noel's dog Keira is rushed into the practice with sickness and diarrhoea. The team also treats River, a Border terrier puppy who has fractured both back legs, and Noel makes a surprise visit home to Ireland.(n)

programme.title: First Dates
programme.desc: Festive edition of the restaurant-based dating show in which Fred and his team open up the restaurant to help 10 new singletons find love in time for Christmas. Operations manager Yasmin, 29, is matched with 31-year-old dental practice manager Ryan, while 59-year-old Mandi is looking for someone with whom to enjoy. Will 65-year-old antique expert Robert be to her taste? Make-up artist Sophie, 24, sits down with 34-year-old window cleaner and self-proclaimed traditional gentleman Mehmet, while embroidery designer Scott is partnered with gallery assistant Jim. The pair discuss culture and the arts, but will they see the beauty in each other?.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Wildest Weather

programme.title: Gogglebox
programme.desc: The nation's favourite armchair critics share their opinions on what they have been watching during the week, including Strictly Come Dancing, Planet Earth II, First Dates, Rillington Place, David Blaine: Beyond Magic, The Big Life Fix with Simon Reeve, When Phillip Met Prince Philip and White Christmas.(n)

programme.title: The Dog Rescuers with Alan Davies
programme.desc: Alan Davies presents another seasonal special edition of the animal welfare series. This time, staff at Harmsworth Animal Hospital treat a three-year-old English bull terrier with a worrying lump, and a Yorkshire terrier with a badly broken leg. At South Godstone Animal Centre, displaced puppy Obi needs a new home before Christmas. RSCPA Inspector Anthony Joynes rescues a spaniel that has been abandoned in a freezing house, but things do not look so good for Pudding, an elderly shih-tzu that needs some special attention in order to survive past Christmas.(n)

Plus, an acrimonious divorce in Chessington comes to a head when the estranged wife obtains a writ to reclaim the house, and an off-licence owner in Hampshire with unpaid rent of more than £5,000 battles to keep his business open just as everything shuts down for the holidays.(n)

programme.title: The Crew
programme.desc: In this dark comedy, a group of retirees wants to save their homes -- but they're not typical senior citizens trying to make the most of their Social Security checks. Four aging former mobsters -- Joey "Bats" Pistella (Burt Reynolds), Bobby Bartellemeo (Richard Dreyfuss), Mike the Brick (Dan Hedaya), and Tony "The Mouth" Donato (Seymour Cassel) -- live in the same rundown Miami apartment complex, the Raj Mahal. New owners hope to clear out the current tenants and replace them with a younger, more lucrative clientele. But the veteran gangsters don't want to move, so to scrape up the extra rent money, they take a job executing the father of a Miami mob boss. They happen to know he's already dead, so all they have to do is make it look like they did the hit. Their problems start when loudmouthed ladies' man Tony tells too much to Ferris (Jennifer Tilly), a stripper, and soon she's talked him into murdering her mother (Lainie Kazan) in exchange for her silence. The Crew also features Carrie-Anne Moss as a detective and Jeremy Piven as a mob kingpin out to avenge his father's death(n)

programme.title: The Man with Two Brains
programme.desc: Zany horror spoof about a talented brain surgeon trapped in marriage to a malicious wife whose affections are shared with everyone but her husband. A serial elevator killer is on the loose, and the good doctor finds himself in love with the disembodied brain of one of the killer's victims. All he needs is a body to put it in(n)

programme.title: Who Wants to Be a Millionaire
programme.desc: Although the once-hot game show Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? had lost its luster as a prime-time ABC offering, the producers felt that there was enough life left in the property to warrant a Monday-through-Friday syndicated version. Taking over from the earlier series' host Regis Philbin was Meredith Vieira of The View. To make certain that the series would not be bankrupted after its first week on the air, the questions posed to contestants were considerably harder than those on the prime-time incarnation. Also, the famous "fastest finger" round was eliminated, taking some of the pressure off the contestants when they struggled to come up with answers. The most noteworthy change from the original version was the absence of Regis Philbin's familiar catchphrases: One would never hear Meredith Vieira chime in with the legendary "Is that your final answer?" The syndicated Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? was launched on September 16, 2002(n)

programme.title: Antwone Fisher
programme.desc: Antwone Fisher, a young navy man, is forced to see a psychiatrist after a violent outburst against a fellow crewman. During the course of treatment a painful past is revealed and a new hope begins(n)

programme.title: Under Siege 2: Dark Territory
programme.desc: Ryback is taking a train holiday from Denver to Los Angeles with his recently orphaned teenage niece when their break is rudely interrupted by a megalomaniac terrorist. The baddie in question is Travis Dane, who has gained control of the terrifyingly potent, space-based super weapon that he helped design. After being sacked by the US government, he's thrown his lot in with a shady Middle Eastern organisation that's out to destroy the eastern seaboard of the United States. Dane's team of merciless thugs take control of the train, from where the destructive satellite can be operated without detection, as long as the locomotive doesn't stop. But they're not counting on the wily ex-serviceman, nor his resolve to keep his niece safe from harm(n)

programme.title: The Transporter
programme.desc: For the right price, ex-Special Forces officer Frank Martin will take anything anywhere. He just has three rules: no changes to the plan; no real names; no opening the package... until one package starts to move. Inside it is the beautiful Lai and, although Martin delivers her to the unscrupulous Darren "Wall Street" Bettencourt, his conscience soon gets the better of him and he decides to track down Wall Street and his masters and rescue Lai…(n)

programme.title: Panic Room
programme.desc: Jodie Foster is put through the wringer by suspense director David Fincher ("Seven") in this taut thriller. When thieves break into their Manhattan brownstone, a single mother (Foster) and her daughter hide in a high-tech, fortified "safe room." But as it turns out, the money the crooks are after is in that room. Kristen Stewart, Forest Whitaker, Dwight Yoakam, Jared Leto(n)

programme.title: Scream 3
programme.desc: In Hollywood, Sidney Prescott must once again confront her demons when the stars of a horror movie sequel based on her life begin to die(n)

programme.desc: Fast-paced action with Steven Seagal and Keenen Ivory Wayans working together to solve a chain of mysterious killings. Contains flashing images(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike XXL
programme.desc: Retired male stripper Magic Mike (Channing Tatum) decides to help his friends put on one last show, as the crew embark on a road trip to Myrtle Beach to perform at an exotic-dance convention. Along the way, they brighten the lives of several women, including an aspiring photographer (Amber Heard) and a diva (Jada Pinkett Smith) from Mike's past(n)

programme.title: Entourage
programme.desc: An A-list actor and his posse of best buds navigate the perils and pleasures of Hollywood life. Based on the HBO series(n)

programme.title: Phone Booth

programme.title: The Last Witch Hunter
programme.desc: An immortal witch hunter faces off against the Queen Witch who has returned from the dead in a battle where the fate of humanity hangs in the balance(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike

programme.title: Planet of the Apes
programme.desc: A US spacecraft crash lands on a desolate looking planet, stranding the astronauts in a world dominated by apes 2000 years into the future. The astronauts are captured by a pack of savage hunters -uniformed gorillas on horseback and are separated from each other. Only the group's leader Taylor survives, and severely injured in the throat, is taken to an animal hospital where he is incarcerated after receiving primitive medical treatment. As he recovers consciousness he is amazed to find that he is held prisoner by a society dominated by intelligent apes, an autocratic social order in which humans are feared they're more slaves than beasts -- and treated as such(n)

programme.title: Speed Racer
programme.desc: A young driver, Speed Racer, aspires to be champion of the racing world with the help of his family and his high-tech Mach 5 automobile(n)

programme.title: Evan Almighty
programme.desc: Evan Baxter is a rising congressman with a bright future and his goal to change the world. God hears this message and decides to give him a hand. Delivering Evan the material and the animals, he sets Evan the task of building an ark. After trying to ignore God as much as possible, Evan eventually goes ahead with the plan, even if the other Congressmen and his family thinks he's mad(n)

programme.title: Furious 7
programme.desc: In this high-octane thrill ride, a tight-knit gang of street racers must battle the brother of a defeated nemesis and rescue a software genius from terrorists. The film is dedicated to series regular Paul Walker, who died halfway through production(n)

programme.title: First Date, Last Date
programme.desc: A couple destined to be together find each other at the worst possible time. A finalist in the Short Film Competition at the 2015 American Black Film Festival(n)

programme.title: Resident Evil
programme.desc: Alice leads a team of commandos into the multi-national Umbrella Corporation's locked-down bunker, which is controlled by the main computer, The Red Queen. The unit is sealed because of a virus that gassed all the staff but, as Alice and her team discover, the virus has re-animated them. Now, as well as facing the computer's weaponry, they must tackle the living dead to prevent the virus escaping into the outside world. Paul W Anderson's horror thriller is based on the successful computer game(n)

programme.title: Victor Frankenstein
programme.desc: This reimagining of the Frankenstein mythos focuses on Igor, the assistant of Victor Frankenstein. When the mad scientist builds an undead creature that soon becomes a grave danger, it's up to Igor to save Frankenstein from both the monster and himself(n)

programme.title: Crimson Tide
programme.desc: Undersea suspense drama. The world stands at the brink of war after a Russian nationalist seizes control of a nuclear missile base. On board a US nuclear submarine, tensions between the captain and his new first officer are heightened when a confusing message is received. The resulting quarrel about whether or not to launch missiles divides the crew and leads to mutiny(n)

programme.title: Krampus
programme.desc: After losing his faith in Christmas and tearing apart his letter to Santa, a young boy (Emjay Anthony) accidentally summons the malevolent holiday demon Krampus. The following day, his family awaken to find that a massive blizzard has knocked out the power in their house, and they are soon forced to fight for survival as the fearsome folklore creature and his minions proceed to wreak havoc on the dysfunctional clan. Adam Scott, Toni Collette, and David Koechner co-star in this hybrid of black comedy and horror from director Michael Dougherty (Trick 'r Treat)(n)

programme.title: Planet of the Apes
programme.desc: Tim Burton called his interpretation of the classic film a "re-imagining" and it incorporates both stunning visual effects and very human (and simian) emotions. Mark Wahlberg plays astronaut Leo Davidson, whipped through space and time to a world where apes and gorillas rule the humans. Captured, he is nurtured by Ari and hunted by General Thade as he leads a rebel group of humans and chimpanzees in search of his downed craft. This is his only hope of escape and the planet's only hope of shaking off the tyranny of the gorillas, to allow peaceful humans and chimpanzees to co-exist. Homages include a cameo from Charlton Heston, with a re-phrasing of his most famous line from the original(n)

programme.title: Frank Miller's Sin City

programme.desc: Singer and former X Factor judge Cheryl takes part in the popular genealogy documentary, in which famous faces trace their family trees. The one-time Girls Aloud member knows little about her heritage, beyond her sense as a true Geordie, so she sets out to trace her roots in the North East. On her father's side she discovers a seafaring ancestor and a family tragedy. On her mother's side, she learns the story of her long-forgotten great-grandfather, a soldier in the First World War who fought in one of the most famous battles on the Western Front.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: Christmas City
programme.desc: Rav Wilding and Hayley Hassall investigate what it takes to deliver a special Christmas for shoppers, workers, residents and tourists in Greater Manchester.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Tim Wonnacott is joined by experts Caroline Hawley and Colin Young as two teams of engaged couples search for items in Builth Wells, Wales, before heading to an auction in Shrewsbury to see if they can make a profit.(n)

programme.title: Fern Britton Meets
programme.desc: The boxer discusses his sporting career and how he was able to recover from a life of drug abuse and depression when he converted to Christianity 10 years ago.(n)

programme.title: Underdog
programme.desc: A mad scientist kidnaps a beagle to use as a guinea pig in his deranged experiments. But an accidental injection leaves the mutt with awe-inspiring superpowers, which he uses to foil the deranged inventor's plans to take over a city. Comedy adventure, starring Peter Dinklage and James Belushi, and featuring the voices of Jason Lee and Amy Adams.(n)

programme.title: Robot Wars
programme.desc: Dara O Briain and Angela Scanlon present another round of battles in the arena. An untested robot built by a cardiologist and his two sons makes a surprising impact in the arena, while a builder from Northampton wheels out an impressive looking axe-wielding robot. Plus, judge Sethu Vijayakumar discusses his work with Nasa, designing robots to explore Mars.(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Sarah Moore and her team transforms a hunk of wood, a Victorian architrave, a floral carpet and some leather cushions in the hope of making a profit.(n)

programme.title: Daily Politics
programme.desc: Parliamentary proceedings interspersed with discussions, interviews and filmed reports from around the country. Presented by Jo Coburn.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the lives of leopards and their cubs in East Africa. While other big cats such as tigers, cheetahs and lions struggle to survive, leopards thrive across half the world and even manage to live undercover in farms and cities in Africa and Asia. Jonathan Scott narrates.(n)

programme.title: Nigella's Christmas Kitchen
programme.desc: Food writer Nigella Lawson reveals her philosophy for coping with the stress of Christmas cooking. In the first programme she prepares festive favourites that can be made in advance and frozen, including mince pies, lamb tagine with dates and pomegranates, as well as roast pumpkin and sweet potato soup with a Stilton swirl.(n)

programme.title: This Farming Life
programme.desc: The early winter is a time of year that brings new life on the farms and Martin's sheds are full of pregnant cows - but there are two he is particularly concerned about. The vet arrives on Lewis to do an annual blood test on Sandy's Highland cattle during a Force 11 gale, while back on the mainland Sybil nearly gets carried away when she and George head to market to buy rams to breed with their ewes.(n)

programme.title: A Place to Call Home
programme.desc: Anna is relieved when Gino believes she miscarried, and they spend the night together in the cottage before telling their families of their intention to marry. James sees a psychiatrist who agrees to treat his sexuality, Elizabeth worries that Regina is getting closer to discovering the truth about Sarah's past, and Jack is stunned to learn that he is Anna's father. However, a bigger shock is in store for those at Ash Park when a body is found in the river. Romantic drama, starring Marta Dusseldorp.(n)

programme.title: Full Steam Ahead
programme.desc: The historians reveal how the railways transformed the British diet, rescuing a nation that was struggling to feed itself. Alex Langlands and Peter Ginn discover how the mass transportation of livestock gave birth to the traditional British roast, and Ruth Goodman is in Whitby, which became a thriving fishing town thanks to the North Yorkshire Moors Railway supplying its kippers. Plus, Hampshire's watercress line, which brought nutritional salad to the masses, and how the use of steam-powered engines revolutionised production at Britain's oldest brewery.(n)

programme.title: Gareth Malone's Great Choir Reunion
programme.desc: Gareth continues his mission to reunite the remainder of all the choirs he has formed over the past 10 years. He tracks down some of the best singers from the South Oxhey Community Choir, the Military Wives and the nine workplace choirs he formed for the competition Sing While You Work. That's followed by frenzied preparations and rehearsals for the reunion concert. He may be able to bring together these singers from different groups across the country, but will he manage to get them singing together as a choir of choirs?.(n)

programme.title: The Real Marigold Hotel
programme.desc: The group settle into life in their base in Jaipur, India, as Wayne Sleep and Bobby George have a cut-throat shave, Patti Boulaye and Miriam Margoyles visit a local laundrywoman, and Jan Leeming attends a psychic guru and is astounded at his profound observations on her life. To end the second week, the celebrities take a 150-mile trip to the Taj Mahal, some by train and others by chauffeur-driven car, and the sheer beauty of the world's most impressive monument to love leaves Miriam in tears.(n)

programme.title: Mary Berry's Absolute Christmas Favourites
programme.desc: The Great British Bake Off judge and food writer draws on her wealth of cookery knowledge to share a selection of indulgent recipes for the festive period, with simple tips to ensure delicious results. In the first of two programmes, Mary updates her mother's Christmas Eve fish pie, makes a raised chicken and ham pie perfect for Boxing Day lunch and prepares two desserts - a blackberry and apple crumble tart and a chocolate mousse cake. Mary also visits a cheese-maker in Nottinghamshire using centuries-old methods to produce Stilton, while chocolatier William Curley takes her breath away with a spectacular Christmas buche de Noel.(n)

programme.title: Christmas University Challenge
programme.desc: It's the second match of the Christmas quiz with two teams of graduates fighting it out for a place in the semi-finals. Playing are the University of Kent with presenter Paul Ross and journalist Shiulie Ghosh, and the University of Sussex with news presenter Dermot Murnaghan and comedienne Hattie Hayridge. Jeremy Paxman asks the questions.(n)

programme.title: MasterChef: The Professionals
programme.desc: The four remaining chefs head into the final week of challenges, starting off with a once in a lifetime opportunity to take part in the prestigious culinary event, The Chef's Table. Cooking for some of the biggest names in modern gastronomy, such as Simon Rogan, Claude Bosi and Michael Caines, the chefs showcase their talents in an attempt to get their food noticed by some of the leading figures in the UK culinary scene.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: Gregg Wallace, Cherry Healey and Ruth Goodman present a festive edition in which they visit places where traditional Christmas items roll off the production line. Gregg goes to Britain's biggest cake factory, where 180 million mince pies are produced each year, and pitches in on the Yule log conveyor belt, while Cherry discovers where tinsel and wrapping paper are made. Meanwhile, Ruth discovers the history of Christmas crackers.(n)

programme.title: Live at the Apollo
programme.sub-title: Live at the Apollo: Christmas Special.
programme.desc: Another leading performer on the stand-up circuit plays host in this show recorded before a packed house at London's Hammersmith Apollo, warming up the audience and then introducing routines by fellow comedians ready to share their light-hearted views on modern life.(n)

programme.title: Upstart Crow
programme.desc: An outbreak of the plague in London prompts Will and his friends to escape to the Shakespeare family home in Stratford-upon-Avon. On their way to Warwickshire, they meet three witches (Mina Anwar, Sarah Finigan and Christine Ozanne Weird) who have some surprising predictions to make about the playwright's future, leading to a very serious case of house envy. Comedy by Ben Elton about William Shakespeare's family and professional lives, starring David Mitchell as the Bard, with Harry Enfield, Paula Wilcox and Liza Tarbuck.(n)

programme.title: NFL This Week
programme.desc: Action from the 15th round of fixtures, which included Chicago Bears v Green Bay Packers, Denver Broncos v New England Patriots, and Dallas Cowboys v Tampa Bay Buccaneers.(n)

programme.title: The Apprentice
programme.desc: The final five are told to brush up on their business plans, for this week's task is the old favourite in which the candidates undergo gruelling interviews by Alan Sugar's trusted associates, who leave no stone unturned as they scrutinise the hopefuls' CVs and professional capabilities. It's a nerve-racking process for the hopefuls, as egos are bruised, lies are uncovered and personalities are attacked. When it's all over, the advisers give their opinions in the boardroom before Alan Sugar decides which hopefuls he wants in the final, shattering the others' dreams with a quick poke of his finger and those immortal words.(n)

programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are
programme.desc: Liz Bonnin takes part in the popular genealogy documentary, in which famous faces trace their family trees. The wildlife presenter describes herself as `a mongrel' - the result of her parents' lineages on the Caribbean islands of Trinidad and Martinique. In Trinidad, she goes in search of the first of her maternal ancestors to arrive on the island from India. Liz then heads to Martinique, where her paternal ancestors are said to have owned plantations - and slaves. However, what she uncovers is more complicated than she could have imagined.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: Christmas City
programme.desc: Rav Wilding and Hayley Hassall investigate what it take to deliver a special Christmas for the shoppers, workers, residents and tourists in Greater Manchester.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: At Epsom Downs Racecourse in Surrey, antiques experts David Harper and Natasha Raskin help two teams find interesting items to take to auction and hopefully make a profit. Presented by Tim Wonnacott.(n)

programme.title: Coastal Path
programme.desc: Traversing the rugged and mysterious north Cornish coast, explorer Paul Rose's first stop is Morwenstow, where he squeezes into the Trust's smallest property, the Hawker's Hut. Built in the 1800s by opium-smoking poet Reverend Hawker, it is popular with walkers who add their own graffiti. Next, Paul enjoys a tour of the wild and majestic Tintagel Castle, before heading to Padstow where the Mayday 'Obby 'Oss celebrations are in full swing. Paul is then put through his paces by a group of youngsters training to be surf lifesavers at Newquay's Fistral beach.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The first of the London and South East heats sees returning contender Mark Froydenlund and newcomers Russell Bateman and Ronnie Murray prepare their starters, which feature a refined and contemporary version of bubble and squeak, an unusual combination of haddock, sausage meat and scallops, and a historical recipe for rook pie.(n)

programme.title: Flight of the Navigator
programme.desc: A boy mysteriously disappears in 1978, and is found eight years later, having not aged a day. He escapes being experimented on by government scientists by taking off in a crashed alien spaceship. With the help of the robot pilot, he tries to find out what has happened to him and if he can get back home. Sci-fi adventure, starring Joey Cramer and Veronica Cartwright, with the voice of Paul Reubens.(n)

programme.title: Robot Wars
programme.desc: Dara O Briain and Angela Scanlon present more battles in the arena, including a robot designed by a nine-year-old girl, which comes complete with a huge pink axe. Other entrants include a team of students from Falkirk whose robot is made of wood and has a petrol engine, and a family team with an ingenious creation made up of parts sourced from their local scrapyard.(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Sarah Moore and her team find four tip-bound treasures found in Greater Manchester and the West Midlands, and transform them into profitable pieces.(n)

programme.title: Equestrian
programme.desc: Lee McKenzie presents action from the prestigious event, which was staged over seven days at the Olympia Grand Hall in London, and featured the latest round of the FEI World Cup. With commentary by Michael Tucker and Andy Austin.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: The truth about the Africanised honey bee, more commonly known as the killer bee, one of the most successful invaders and a cause of devastation in the natural world. The programme analyses whether there is a way of taming this lethal force of nature.(n)

programme.title: Nigella's Christmas Kitchen
programme.desc: Cookery writer Nigella Lawson demonstrates how to make food-based festive gifts, including Italian bonbons and chilli jam. She also prepares a pre-Christmas brunch featuring an espresso martini, cheese and onion strata, glazed and toasted vanilla cake `brioche' and an antioxidant-packed fruit salad.(n)

programme.title: This Farming Life
programme.desc: Christmas is looming, and in Inverness, Martin Irvine's sheds are now full of cows and their newborn calves. One was born prematurely and with such a low weigh his chances of survival don't look good. Cameras also follow the drama in Argyll where the weather takes a turn for the worse, just when Sybil and George Macpherson must load more than two tonnes of fleeces into a haulage lorry.(n)

programme.title: World's Sneakiest Animals
programme.desc: Naturalist Chris Packham observes the devious tactics and sneaky tricks that some animals carry out in order to survive. New, ground-breaking science helps reveal astonishing visual trickery, from illusionist zebras to vanishing geckos and shape-shifting cuttlefish. Mischievous mimics, from snakes to baby birds disguised as caterpillars, and a lioness who looks like a male lion are also highlighted. The world's ultimate con artists can even rely on sneaky strategies against their own kind, such as the monkey that cheats its family and the lizard that fakes its death.(n)

programme.title: Full Steam Ahead
programme.desc: The historians take a trip on the Flying Scotsman, arguably the most famous locomotive in the world, along its original route connecting London and Edinburgh - the two most important financial capitals of the Empire. Peter Ginn explores how the railways revolutionised the delivery of mail across Britain, he and Alex Langlands learn about the first electronic communication service - more than 100 years before the arrival of email - and Ruth finds out about the role of the wheeltapper. Plus, why do some railway clocks have more than one minute hand?.(n)

programme.title: Back in Time for Christmas
programme.desc: Part one of two. The Robshaws time-travel through six decades of festive nostalgia, beginning by experiencing what the holiday season was like in the 1940s, '50s and '60s. A wartime Christmas has them embracing the make-do and mend spirit for presents and sitting down to ox heart for dinner, with a pudding made primarily of grated potato. The 1950s brings ham with tinned peaches, canapes, cocktails and the first televised Queen's speech, while youngest child Fred receives a 1960s gift of a chocolate smoking set. Giles Coren and Polly Russell present.(n)

programme.title: The Real Marigold Hotel
programme.desc: The group enjoy the final week of their experiment in Jaipur and attends one of the highlights of the Hindu calendar, the Ganesh Chaturthi festival, a riot of colour and noise, packed with people, floats and elephants. They also make a trip to Varanasi, one of the holiest cities in India, where Hindus come to be purified by the waters of the Ganges and to cremate their dead in the hope they have the best chance of reaching Nirvana. Back in Jaipur, Bobby and Jan go in search for property, with Bobby keen to find somewhere to buy and Jan falling in love with the idea of renting an apartment in a haveli amongst a local family.(n)

programme.title: Mary Berry's Absolute Christmas Favourites
programme.desc: Part two of two. The Great British Bake Off judge demonstrates five indulgent but easy recipes for a stress-free Christmas Day and an enviable feast, beginning with mulled wine and mini filo beef Wellington canapes to get guests in the festive mood. For the main dinner, she roasts a turkey crown and serves it with all the trimmings, before preparing her own simple take on the traditional mince pie. Mary also visits some specialist artisans getting ready for a busy festive period and heads to Hampton Court Palace, in south-west London, to find out whether her Christmas in any way resembles those celebrated by the Tudors.(n)

programme.title: Christmas University Challenge
programme.sub-title: City - University of London v Newcastle University.
programme.desc: Jeremy Paxman presents the third match of the Christmas series, in which alumni from City, University of London take on former students of the University of Newcastle. Among the graduates representing City are journalist Samira Ahmed and Chair of ACAS Brendan Barber, while Newcastle's champions include music industry veteran Wilko Johnson, and TV presenter Charlie Webster.(n)

programme.title: MasterChef: The Professionals
programme.desc: In the penultimate episode, the four remaining chefs battle for an all-important place in the final three, each cooking a dish that defines and delivers a taste of a landscape close to their hearts. With one of the four chefs leaving the competition, the remaining three head to Oslo to work with groundbreaking young chef Esben Holmboe Bang. The chefs get to grips with his food philosophy and create a stunning dish to impress Esben, before taking part in a service in his Michelin-starred restaurant, Maaemo.(n)

programme.title: The Big Life Fix with Simon Reeve
programme.desc: The team build life-saving equipment for brothers Morgan and Aiden, who suffer from cystic fibrosis, turning part of their daily physiotherapy routine into a computer game to help motivate the boys through their therapy. Later, the inventors develop technology that will give a partially-sighted mum the freedom to enjoy the outdoors, and create a supportive helmet for Rosie, a young girl with a brain condition that requires her to wear protective headwear. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Insert Name Here
programme.desc: New series. Host Sue Perkins and the team captains Josh Widdicombe and Richard Osman are joined by guests Danny Baker, Sara Pascoe, Deborah Meaden and Kate Williams for a festive edition of the comedy panel game, with fiendish facts about the Queen's Christmas Speech, Delia Smith's Christmas Cooking and the original Father Christmas, St Nicholas.(n)

programme.title: The Premier League Show
programme.desc: Gabby Logan presents the magazine programme featuring news and action from the Premier League, plus interviews with the country's biggest football stars.(n)

programme.title: A Life on Screen
programme.sub-title: Sir Lenny Henry - A Life on Screen.
programme.desc: After being honoured with the Special Award at this year's Baftas, the actor and comedian reveals the story behind his success. Lenny delves into the archives to showcase work from his 41 years in showbusiness - from his first TV appearance on New Faces in 1975 up to his present day achievements in the theatre. Featuring interviews with people who have helped shape his career, including Richard Curtis, Kim Fuller, Michael Grade, Trevor McDonald and Chris Tarrant.(n)

programme.title: Indian Hill Railways
programme.desc: The lives and loves of workers on the Nilgiri Mountain Railway, a steam-powered line that runs through the south Indian jungle up to a hill station once known as Snooty Ooty. Happily married guard Ivan worries about the romantic prospects of ticket inspector Jenni, while engineer Shivani works to make sure a locomotive is ready for the annual Black Beauty competition, which will pick the best engine on the line.(n)

programme.title: How the Wild West Was Won with Ray Mears
programme.desc: The adventurer explores how the Great Plains - 500,000-square miles of flat, treeless grassland - became the setting for some of the Wild West's most dramatic events. Ray joins members of the Blackfeet Indian tribe as they demonstrate bare-back riding skills before undertaking a ritual buffalo hunt and sacrifice. At a cattle auction in Dodge City, Kansas, he reveals stories about the railways and cow-towns before learning about the life of an iconic figure - the cowboy.(n)

programme.title: Digging for Britain
programme.desc: Alice Roberts visits archaeological digs in the east of Britain. Finds include new revelations from a 3,000-year-old perfectly preserved village near Cambridgeshire, and the theatre where Shakespeare premiered Rome and Juliet. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Inca: Masters of the Clouds
programme.desc: Dr Jago Cooper presents the concluding edition of the two-part documentary, as he argues that it was a clash of world views that destroyed the Incas, not just a clash of weapons. He travels from Peru to the far north of the ancient empire's former territory in Ecuador to reveal how the strengths of the civilisation also led to its downfall. He charts the impact of the Spanish conquest in the 16th century and the legacy the Incas left behind.(n)

programme.title: The Incredible Story of Marie Antoinette's Watch with Nicholas Parsons
programme.desc: The Just a Minute host explores the life and work of Swiss horologist Abraham-Louis Breguet and goes in search of his most famous timepiece, which is valued at up to $100m.(n)

programme.title: Timeshift
programme.sub-title: Timeshift: Booze, Beans and Bhajis - The Story of the Corner Shop.
programme.desc: Babita Sharma explores the growing and shifting fortunes of corner shops to discover why this unsung hero has been at the centre of ordinary lives for more than 70 years. Featuring contributions by comedian Sanjeev Singh Kholi and actor Nitin Ganatra, Babita uses the shop as a way to explore the social fabric of Britain - from economic change to immigration.(n)

Stationmaster Sanjay hopes for a promotion, his boss Bataljit expects a transfer, while teacher John Whitmarsh-Knight is searching for a home - and every one of them is anticipating snow. programme.desc: The final leg of this exploration of the UK's Overseas Territories begins in the Caribbean, where Stewart McPherson finds some unexpected wildlife. Stewart also visits the Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus, along with Gibraltar, the present home of Barbary Macaques, Europe's only wild colony of monkeys. Last in the series.(n)

A team of international engineers race to build the new steel structure, but radiation levels make it almost impossible for workers to build right on top of the old reactor. The team face difficult challenges as they attempt to erect this new steel mega-structure and move it into place.(n)

programme.desc: In a Christmas special first broadcast in 1982, Cockney music duo Chas Hodges and Dave Peacock entertain an audience of Londoners in a replica of an East End pub, performing festive tunes as well as songs including Ain't No Pleasing You, Goodnight Irene and Wish I Could Write a Love Song. programme.title: Snow Angels

Michael Angarano, Nicky Katt, Jeannetta Arnette, Griffin Dunne, Tom Noonan. Directed by David Gordon Green(n)

programme.desc: In this high-octane thrill ride, a tight-knit gang of street racers must battle the brother of a defeated nemesis and rescue a software genius from terrorists. The film is dedicated to series regular Paul Walker, who died halfway through production(n)

programme.desc: Well-meaning but witless ex-con 'H' McDunnough causes pandemonium when he steals one of Arizona's famous newborn quintuplets for his infertile wife(n)

programme.title: Hollywood Ending
programme.desc: A down-on-his luck auteur gets one more chance at the big time -- provided his neuroses don't swallow him whole -- in Woody Allen's 33rd feature release, Hollywood Ending. Allen plays Val Waxman, a one-time cinematic genius who's resorted to taking advertisement work to pay the bills for himself and his airhead live-in girlfriend, Lori (Debra Messing). Val finds his luck is about to change, however, when he receives the script for The City Never Sleeps , a period noir set against the backdrop of 1940s New York City. It seems his ex-wife, Ellie (Tea Leoni), now an executive at Galaxy Pictures, has been pulling for him to direct the picture, claiming he's the only man who can do justice to the script. She even manages to convince her boyfriend, Hal (Treat Williams), Galaxy's high-powered studio head, to take a chance on Val's "unique vision." Just when the cameras are ready to roll, however, Val finds that unique vision in jeopardy -- literally -- as he's struck with a psychosomatic case of blindness. When physicians and psychiatrists fail to cure him, Val contrives a scheme to forge ahead with the picture, for fear of blowing his one last chance at greatness. Hollywood Ending co-stars George Hamilton and Mark Rydell(n)

programme.title: The Simpsons Movie
programme.desc: America's favourite family make their debut on the big screen in David Silverman's comedy. When Homer rescues a pig from certain death, little does he realise the full consequences of his action: Springfield will be isolated from the world by a gargantuan glass dome. It's the only way the government can prevent the pollution that he caused escaping to the outside world and creating a race of six-eyed squirrels. The townsfolk, armed with torches and pitchforks, are soon after him, and the family have to flee to Alaska. But even Homer knows he must return to do the right thing... Warning: contains full frontal male nudity(n)

programme.title: Adam Sandler's Eight Crazy Nights
programme.desc: Come celebrate the joy and togetherness of the Hanukkah season with Adam Sandler -- yeah, that Adam Sandler -- in this raucous animated comedy written and produced in collaboration with the noted funnyman. Davey Stone (voice of Adam Sandler) is a twentysomething man with a short temper and a reputation for causing trouble who lives in the small New England town of Dukesberry. Davey has a particularly bad attitude about the holiday season, and on the first night of Hanukkah, he goes on a tear that lands him in front of a judge (voice of Norm Crosby). The judge, who has dealt with Davey before, is prepared to send him to prison, but Whitey (also voiced by Sandler), an eccentric but kindly old man, persuades the judge to give him a chance to turn Davey into a more responsible citizen. Davey doesn't think much of Whitey's charitable nature, but when his trailer home burns down, he's forced to move in with Whitey and his perpetually nervous sister, Eleanore (also voiced by Sandler...spotting a trend here?). Between Whitey and Eleanore's nonstop kvetching and the reappearance of his old girlfriend Jennifer (voice of Jackie Titone), Davey is being driven to distraction by the Hanukkah season, but in time Whitey learns the truth about why Davey has such a problem with the Festival of Lights. Adam Sandler's Eight Crazy Nights also includes eight new songs co-written by Sandler; he duets with bluegrass star Alison Krauss on "Long Ago."(n)

programme.title: Earth's Natural Wonders
programme.sub-title: Earth's Natural Wonders: Living on the Edge.
programme.desc: The first of two programmes in which cameras explore some of the most inhospitable places on the planet and the people who live there, including a team of Sherpa roping a route on Mount Everest's notorious Khumbu Icefall and, on the slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro, farmers fight pitched battles to save their crops from marauding elephants. In the Amazon rainforest, two boys undergo a rite of passage involving hundreds of ants with the most painful stings on Earth, and conservationists in the Grand Canyon try to ensure the survival of one of America's few surviving condor chicks.(n)

programme.title: Earth's Natural Wonders
programme.desc: The second of two documentaries profiling some of the world's most expansive - and inhospitable - landscapes, and the people who live there. A fisherman in Zambia faces off against crocodiles and risks being swept to his death as he tries to make a living above the imposing Victoria Falls, and in the Amazon, a giant fish offers salvation to a hungry family that calls the river home. A boy's future hangs on the outcome of a single horse race in the vast grasslands of the Steppe, and in a European salt marsh, a young man duels with a savage bull in a centuries-old battle of wills.(n)

programme.title: The Mekong River with Sue Perkins
programme.desc: The comedienne and Great British Bake Off presenter embarks on a 3,000-mile journey along the Southeast Asian river, exploring lives and landscapes on the point of dramatic change. She begins in Vietnam, where she meets traditional river people caught up in a new capitalist revolution, before trying her hand as a noodle saleswoman and prawn farmer. Continuing to Cambodia, she is moved by the tale of a survivor of Pol Pot's genocide, before bonding with the residents of a floating village whose survival depends on the bounty of Tonle Sap, the largest freshwater lake in Asia.(n)

programme.title: The Mekong River with Sue Perkins
programme.desc: The comedienne embarks on the most emotional leg of her journey along the Southeast Asian river as she witnesses how deforestation and wildlife crime are stripping Cambodia of its last wild places. She goes on a raid with a rapid response rescue team searching for trafficked animals and bush meat, as well as helping the unit release macaques and a slow loris back into the wild. She also spends time with the women of the Krung, who live in the remote highlands of Ratanakiri and are one of the tribes most affected by rapid deforestation.(n)

programme.title: The Mekong River with Sue Perkins
programme.desc: The comedienne continues her journey up the Southeast Asian river and reaches Laos, where she meets a fisherman who has taken advantage of the increasing number of tourists by setting up a restaurant on the beach. Sue then heads to Luang Prabang, a town that is now a Unesco world heritage site and famed as the centre of Buddhism, where she spends a day with novice monks. She also visits the Xayaburi hydroelectric dam, which will completely block the flow of the river, bringing economic benefits to Laos and beyond, but harming the livelihoods of tens of millions of people downstream.(n)

programme.title: The Mekong River with Sue Perkins
programme.desc: The comedian concludes her epic journey along the Southeast Asian river as she follows it through China's wildest and most spectacular valleys on her way to the Mekong's source in the Himalayas. With the Chinese economic boom sweeping through these remote regions, Sue reveals how ancient ways of life are changing and asks what China will save of its past. At the end of her 3,000-mile quest, she joins a group of nuns high on the Tibetan Plateau as they make an offering to the gods at the point where the Mekong's waters first filter into the lives of people. Last in the series.(n)

She also spends time with the women of the Krung, who live in the remote highlands of Ratanakiri and are one of the tribes most affected by rapid deforestation.(n)

programme.title: The Mekong River with Sue Perkins
programme.desc: The comedienne continues her journey up the Southeast Asian river and reaches Laos, where she meets a fisherman who has taken advantage of the increasing number of tourists by setting up a restaurant on the beach. Sue then heads to Luang Prabang, a town that is now a Unesco world heritage site and famed as the centre of Buddhism, where she spends a day with novice monks. She also visits the Xayaburi hydroelectric dam, which will completely block the flow of the river, bringing economic benefits to Laos and beyond, but harming the livelihoods of tens of millions of people downstream.(n)

programme.title: The Mekong River with Sue Perkins
programme.desc: The comedian concludes her epic journey along the Southeast Asian river as she follows it through China's wildest and most spectacular valleys on her way to the Mekong's source in the Himalayas. With the Chinese economic boom sweeping through these remote regions, Sue reveals how ancient ways of life are changing and asks what China will save of its past. At the end of her 3,000-mile quest, she joins a group of nuns high on the Tibetan Plateau as they make an offering to the gods at the point where the Mekong's waters first filter into the lives of people. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Hunt
programme.desc: The wildlife series concludes by examining efforts by scientists to ensure the survival of endangered species of carnivores, as the spread of human habitation impacts on the wildest areas of the planet and jeopardises the predators' opportunities to hunt and thrive. The film uses natural history footage to examine the current situation across five continents, revealing the precarious future faced by many of the world's most fascinating species, including lions, tigers, polar bears and blue whales. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Earth's Natural Wonders
programme.sub-title: Earth's Natural Wonders: Living on the Edge.
programme.desc: The first of two programmes in which cameras explore some of the most inhospitable places on the planet and the people who live there, including a team of Sherpa roping a route on Mount Everest's notorious Khumbu Icefall and, on the slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro, farmers fight pitched battles to save their crops from marauding elephants. In the Amazon rainforest, two boys undergo a rite of passage involving hundreds of ants with the most painful stings on Earth, and conservationists in the Grand Canyon try to ensure the survival of one of America's few surviving condor chicks.(n)

programme.title: Earth's Natural Wonders
programme.desc: The second of two documentaries profiling some of the world's most expansive - and inhospitable - landscapes, and the people who live there. A fisherman in Zambia faces off against crocodiles and risks being swept to his death as he tries to make a living above the imposing Victoria Falls, and in the Amazon, a giant fish offers salvation to a hungry family that calls the river home. A boy's future hangs on the outcome of a single horse race in the vast grasslands of the Steppe, and in a European salt marsh, a young man duels with a savage bull in a centuries-old battle of wills.(n)

programme.desc: Chefs Si King and Dave Myers scour the nation to find out what women are cooking for their families over the festive period. programme.desc: Produced by Tom Hanks, written by Aaron Sorkin, and directed by Mike Nichols, this adaptation of George Crile III's incendiary bestseller tells the remarkable story of the Texas congressman whose efforts to prevent the Red Army from overtaking Afghanistan eventually led to the collapse of the Soviet Union while simultaneously fueling the rise of radical Islam. In the early 1980s, a hastily assembled army of Afghan "freedom fighters" achieved the remarkable feat of fending off Soviet invaders despite the fact that the odds were overwhelmingly stacked against them. At the time, Texas congressman Charlie Wilson (Hanks) was a key member of the hugely powerful House Appropriations Committee. Illuminated to the specifics of this remarkable war by a high-profile Houston socialite, Wilson spearheaded an effort to provide hundreds of millions of dollars in weapons and training to the Mujahideen with more than a little help from brilliant but prickly CIA operative Gust Avrokotos(n)

Joining forces with another group of survivors following a terrifying encounter in a seemingly abandoned church, Jim soon learns the truth behind the deserted streets and the menacing creatures that lurk in the shadows. Huffman earned a Best Actress nomination. Kevin Zegers plays the troubled, unsuspecting offspring who joins his parent on a roller-coaster, cross-country road trip. Huffman's husband, William H. Macy, is the executive producer. The film is the directorial debut of Duncan Tucker, who wrote the script(n)

programme.title: Jackpot
programme.desc: Set 100 miles south of the setting of the Polish brothers' first feature, Twin Falls Idaho, Jackpot tells the story of Sunny Holiday Jon Gries, a down-on-his-luck karaoke dweller who has hopes of becoming a country singer. He has abandoned his feisty wife Bobbi (Daryl Hannah) and young daughter to set off on a nine-month road odyssey with his manager Lester Irving (Garrett Morris), in an effort to collect cash at local karaoke gigs. Lester grooms Sunny by choosing what songs he will do, keeping up with what the judges are like, and negotiating with competitors like Sammy Bones (Mac Davis), another traveling hopeful. On his road journey, he encounters several women, including Janice (Peggy Lipton), a club waitress, and Cheryl (Crystal Bernard), whom he takes home after she has an accident in a restroom, only to find himself being enticed by her underage daughter Tangerine (Camellia Clouse). The road trip comes to a stop, however, when Sunny is pulled over by police who claim that his vehicle is stolen and that Bobbi has reported it. Sunny then seeks refuge with brother Tracy (Anthony Edwards) while he decides his next move. Jackpot is the first released film to be shot with the 24P HDTV camera, which was then blown up to Cinemascope 35 mm format(n)

programme.title: Gotcha!
programme.desc: "Gotcha!" is a puerile but popular campus game at UCLA in which students stalk one another armed with paint-spewing pellet guns. Veterinary student Anthony Edwards may not be any great shakes in the classroom, but he's a whiz at Gotcha. His skills come in handy when Edwards, on vacation in Paris, becomes acquainted with the mysterious Linda Fiorentino. She gets him mixed up in international espionage; fortunately, the well-armed spies aren't quite as adept at "Gotcha" as Edwards is. Most of the film was lensed in Paris and Berlin(n)

When Joe brings his daughter Natalie (Hayden Panettiere) to the office with him on Take Our Kids to Work Day, he's humiliated in a spat with company bully Mark McKinney (Patrick Warburton) over a parking space. It's the last straw for the mild-mannered Joe, who challenges McKinney to a rematch, hires a has-been action movie star (Jim Belushi) to instruct him in martial arts, and pays a stylist to make over his wardrobe and hair. As Joe's image improves and the big day approaches, he finds his new self-respecting stance has positive effects in both the workplace, as he lands a long-overdue promotion, and in his romantic life, as both Callie and a cute "wellness coordinator" (Julie Bowen) start warming up to him. programme.desc: After decades of movies about college sports, the bands who take the field at halftime finally get their day in the sun in this musical comedy drama. Devon Miles (Nick Cannon) is a talented young percussionist from Harlem who wins a music scholarship to Atlanta A & T, a prestigious African-American university. For years, Atlanta A & T has won awards for their show-style marching band, who combine expert musicianship (incorporating funk, R&B, and jazz rhythms into the traditional marching band repertoire) with choreography, dancing cheerleaders, and roof-raising showmanship. Dr. Aaron Lee (Orlando Jones), the school's band director, gives Devon a spot in the marching band's drumline, the heart and soul of a show-style band, but discovers Devon's previous musical education hardly meets his usual standard when he learns that his new drummer can't read music. Devon soon earns a reputation as a stubborn individualist within the band, not necessarily a good thing in an ensemble where a strictly unified performance is considers the ideal. Devon's cocksure attitude and streetwise style doesn't mesh very comfortably with Sean Taylor (Leonard Roberts), a disciplined senior who resents the presence of the upstart freshman in the drumline, and things become even less harmonious when Devon begins making a play for Laila (Zoe Saldana), a beautiful girl who is also being courted by Sean. programme.title: The British
programme.desc: How the Norman Conquest in 1066 transformed Britain, as William the Conqueror sought to assert his power over the whole of England by dismantling the Anglo-Saxon aristocracy and crushing regional diversity. The programme explores the human cost of his campaign and the lasting legacy of the social structures established by the Normans, and explains how a spirit of resistance began to foment among the population. Dramatic reconstructions also reveal how the longbow was instrumental in Henry V's famous victory at the battle of Agincourt in 1415. With contributions by Tim Roth, Jeremy Irons, Micky Flanagan and Tracey Emin.(n)

programme.title: The British
programme.desc: How Britain changed during the reign of the Tudor and Stuart monarchs. The programme explores the battles that established England as one of the world's leading naval powers and delves into Henry VIII's feud with the Catholic Church, revealing how he tried to silence dissenting voices. Contributors including Helen Mirren and Ben Kingsley also discover how literature from the period sowed the seeds of revolution, and learn why a riot organised from a prison cell laid the foundations for civil war.(n)

programme.title: The British
programme.desc: How money drove the making of modern Britain, exploring its role in the rebuilding of London following the Great Fire of 1666. The programme investigates how underhanded deals brokered in coffee houses fuelled British prosperity, and exposes how the country profited from dubious practices, including the slave trade, the sex industry and global colonisation. It also explores those who rebelled against the status quo during the period, and discovers how the armed forces countered the threat posed by Napoleon Bonaparte. With contributions by Jeremy Irons, Frank Lampard and Terry Wogan.(n)

programme.title: Billy Madison
programme.desc: A lazy twentysomething lives off his wealthy hotel magnate father. When the old man decides to retire, he begins to question whether his layabout son is suitable to take over the family empire and issues a challenge - he must retake 12 years of school in 24 weeks, or lose everything. Comedy, starring Adam Sandler, Bridgette Wilson, Darren McGavin and Bradley Whitford.(n)

programme.title: Stir Crazy
programme.desc: Two unemployed New Yorkers travel to California in search of fame and fortune. Instead, the hapless duo end up clocking on for a 125-year stint in jail for a bank robbery they did not commit - until a prison rodeo presents them with the chance to make a daring escape. Comedy directed by Sidney Poitier, starring Richard Pryor, Gene Wilder, JoBeth Williams, Craig T Nelson and Georg Stanford Brown.(n)

programme.title: The Truman Show
programme.desc: A man is unaware his uneventful life is really a sham, and his every move is being secretly filmed and broadcast to the world as part of a 24-hour TV soap. However, a series of unforeseen events leads him to question the nature of his existence. Peter Weir's media satire, starring Jim Carrey, Natascha McElhone, Laura Linney, Noah Emmerich and Ed Harris.(n)

programme.title: Get Santa Special
programme.desc: Behind the scenes on the festive comedy about a family that find Santa Claus sleeping in their garage.(n)

programme.title: Sister Act
programme.desc: Nightclub singer Deloris Van Cartier agrees to testify against her gangster boyfriend after witnessing a murder. Placed in protective custody by the authorities, she is less than pleased to discover she is expected to pose as chaste nun Sister Mary Clarence in a convent. Comedy, starring Whoopi Goldberg, Harvey Keitel, Maggie Smith, Bill Nunn and Kathy Najimy.(n)

programme.title: Rushmore
programme.desc: A student causes chaos in an exclusive private school with his temperamental nature - and things go from bad to worse when he develops a crush on a teacher. A wealthy but miserable businessman strikes up a friendship with the troubled teenager, but when he also falls for the same woman, all-out war is declared. Wes Anderson's comedy drama, starring Jason Schwartzman, Bill Murray, Olivia Williams and Brian Cox.(n)

programme.title: Grimsby
programme.desc: Two brothers are separated at birth, the younger growing up to be MI6's top agent while the older becomes a layabout football hooligan. When they are finally reunited, the dim-witted elder sibling ends up helping his brother foil an evil plan that threatens the entire world. Action comedy, starring Sacha Baron Cohen, Mark Strong and Rebel Wilson.(n)

programme.title: Two Night Stand
programme.desc: A woman recovering from a recent break-up has a one-night stand with a stranger she met online. Hoping to leave quietly in the morning, she instead discovers a blizzard has left them both trapped in his apartment, forcing them to spend an awkward but enlightening day together. Romantic comedy, starring Analeigh Tipton and Miles Teller.(n)

programme.title: Loser
programme.desc: A hard-working college student is branded a loser by his roommates, who promptly oust him from their group. When he helps a girl deal with an unpleasant drugs-related experience, he falls madly in love with her - but she only has eyes for a professor. Comedy, starring Jason Biggs, Mena Suvari, Greg Kinnear, Zak Orth, Thomas Sadoski and Dan Aykroyd.(n)

programme.title: Bridget Jones's Diary
programme.desc: A single woman begins a new year with resolutions to find love, quit her bad habits and take a step up the career ladder. Her plans crumble as she tries to deal with her mother's infidelity, get over a passionate fling with her boss and come to terms with her feelings for an uptight lawyer. Romantic comedy based on Helen Fielding's novel, starring Renee Zellweger, Hugh Grant and Colin Firth.(n)

When her impressionable sister Amber falls in love with Wild Bill, one of Uncle Frank's bitter rivals, Hannah spots a way to finally put an end to her misery by using her guile to pit the two men against each other in a vengeful game. Crime thriller, starring Abigail Breslin, Sean Bean and Alexa Vega.(n)

programme.title: Swelter
programme.desc: Ten years after their casino heist, four escaped convicts trace their former partner to a desert town, where he is now a lawman with no memory of his criminal past. Drama, starring Jean-Claude Van Damme, Alfred Molina and Lennie James.(n)

programme.title: Go With Me
programme.desc: A woman returns to the isolated logging community where she grew up, and is stalked by a former cop, who now heads up a criminal organisation in the area that operates above the law. She resolves to take a stand against him, seeking the aid of a retired logger and his sidekick. Thriller based on Castle Freeman Jr's novel, starring Julia Stiles, Anthony Hopkins, Alexander Ludwig and Ray Liotta.(n)

programme.title: American Ultra
programme.desc: Small-town store clerk and unmotivated stoner Mike is enjoying his life with girlfriend Phoebe when his world is suddenly turned upside down. He is unaware he is actually a highly trained, lethal government sleeper agent who has been targeted for assassination, forcing him to summon his inner action-hero in order to survive. Action comedy, starring Jesse Eisenberg and Kristen Stewart.(n)

programme.title: Spooks: The Greater Good
programme.desc: A terrorist escapes custody during a prisoner handover when the convoy he is being transported in is attacked, leading to a CIA operative being killed and relations becoming frayed between British and American intelligence agencies. MI5 officer Will Holloway must team up with disgraced intelligence chief Harry Pearce to track him down before an imminent terrorist attack on London. Spy thriller, starring Kit Harington and Peter Firth.(n)

programme.title: Taken
programme.desc: An American teenager travelling through Europe is abducted by a gang of sex traffickers. However, what the kidnappers do not realise is that the girl's father is a former CIA agent, who employs all his old skills as he searches for the criminals and tries to rescue his daughter. Thriller, starring Liam Neeson, Famke Janssen and Maggie Grace.(n)

programme.title: Snow Day
programme.desc: A New York borough is shut down during a blizzard - and a group of cheeky local children steal a snowplough in a desperate attempt to ensure the roads to their school stay closed as long as possible. Meanwhile, parents all over the city struggle to work out what to do with their offspring. Comedy, starring Chris Elliott, Mark Webber, Jean Smart, Chevy Chase, Iggy Pop, Pam Grier and Zena Grey.(n)

programme.title: Pluto's Christmas Tree

Drama, with Rebecca Harrell, Sam Elliott and Cloris Leachman.(n)

Family comedy, starring Breckin Meyer, Billy Connolly and Jennifer Love Hewitt, with the voices of Bill Murray and Tim Curry.(n)

programme.desc: A lonely boy living in the Scottish Highlands during the Second World War stumbles on a curiously large egg by the water's edge of the local loch. Children's fantasy adventure, based on the book by Dick King-Smith, with Alex Etel, Emily Watson and David Morrissey.(n)

Animated fantasy musical, with the voices of Evan Rachel Wood, Alan Cumming and Kristin Chenoweth.(n)

programme.desc: A curious young bee befriends a number of other insects, despite her hive's strict rules on not associating with outsiders. When some of the Queen bee's royal jelly is stolen, she is accused of the crime and needs the help of her friends to track down the real culprits. Animated adventure based on Waldemar Bonsels' children's book, with the voices of Coco Jack Gillies and Kodi Smit-McPhee.(n)

programme.desc: Three pampered dogs re-imagine themselves as fearless `dogateers' after their owners leave them to guard the family home on Christmas Eve. Festive family adventure, starring Dean Cain, with the voices of Jesse Baget and Danielle Judovits.(n)

Comedy, starring Charles Grodin, Bonnie Hunt, Oliver Platt and David Duchovny.(n)

He asks for his freedom, and spends the next 200 years struggling to come to terms with its humanity. Chris Columbus's sci-fi drama inspired by the books of Isaac Asimov, starring Robin Williams, Sam Neill, Embeth Davidtz and Oliver Platt.(n)

Family comedy, starring Joris Jarsky, Ryan Belleville and Dylan Schmid.(n)

Disney animated fairytale, with the voices of Ilene Woods, William Phipps and Verna Felton.(n)

Fantasy drama, starring Michael Keaton, Kelly Preston, Joseph Cross and Mark Addy.(n)

Animated comedy, with the voices of Martin Freeman, Tim Curry, Joan Collins and Tom Baker.(n)

Fantasy comedy, based on Dr Seuss's children's book, with Jim Carrey, Taylor Momsen, Jeffrey Tambor and Molly Shannon. Anthony Hopkins narrates.(n)
